The President's statement reflects on the 17th anniversary of the Srebrenica genocide, where over 8,000 innocent men and boys were brutally murdered. He emphasizes that justice is being served for the victims, as the perpetrators are being held accountable in courts. The President rejects efforts to distort the atrocity and denies any rationalization or blame towards the victims. He expresses a desire for reconciliation and peaceful coexistence in Bosnia and Herzegovina and the Balkans, as a repudiation of the evil that started the wars in the region. The United States stands with the people of Bosnia and Herzegovina, offering condolences and support for their aspirations for a better future.